 gillingham kings and queens of britain richard i cannon page needed  matthews small sketch of a corssbow above richards inverted shield was probably intended to draw attention to the kins magnanimous forgeiveness of the man who had caused his death a true story first told by roger of howden but with a different thrust it was originally meant to illustrate richards stern unforgiving character since he only pardoned peter basil when he was sure he was going to die but the chronica majora adopted a later popular conception of the generous hearted preux chevalier transforming history into romance suzanne lewis the art of matthew paris in the chronica majora california studies in the history of art vol  university of california press  p   a b andrew holt jonathan phillips crusadesencyclopediacom archived from the original on  december  retrieved  march    stubbs william the constitutional history of england vol  pp–  andrew curry the first holy war us news and world report  april   bundan iyisi şamda kayısıgezi – tatilmilliyet blog blogmilliyetcomtr retrieved  november    jonathan phillips holy warriors a modern history of the crusades london  pp – bibliographyedit addison charles  the history of the knights templars the temple church and the temple london longman brown green and longmans  arnold b   german knighthood – oxford clarendon press isbn   allen brown r   allen browns english castles woodbridge the boydell press isbn   brewer clifford  the death of kings london abson books isbn   cannon john  hargreaves anne eds kings and queens of britain oxford university press   isbn  richard i by john gillingham flori jean  richard the lionheart knight and king translated by jean birrell edinburgh university press isbn   flori jean f richard coeur de lion le roichevalier in french paris biographie payot isbn   gillingham john  richard the lionheart new york times books isbn   gillingham john  richard the lionheart butler and tanner ltd  gillingham john  richard coeur de li