d was at philips court in  during his rebellion against his father henry ii including sleeping in the same bed but according to flori and gillingham such signs of friendship were part of the customs of the time indicating trust and confidence and cannot be interpreted as proof of the homosexuality of either man  bl cotton charter xvi suzanne lewis the art of matthew paris in the chronica majora california studies in the history of art vol  university of california press  p   michel pastoureau heraldry an introduction to a noble tradition thames and hudson ltd  p   woodward and burnett woodwards a treatise on heraldry british and foreign with english and french glossaries p  ailes adrian  the origins of the royal arms of england reading graduate center for medieval studies university of reading pp – charles boutell a c foxdavies ed the handbook to english heraldry th ed   ingle sean  why do england have three lions on their shirts guardiancouk retrieved  april    boutell charles  the art journal london p   flori f pp – french  flori f p  french  holt j c  robin hood p  thames  hudson  a b john gillingham kings and queens of britain richard i cannon page needed  matthews small sketch of a corssbow above richards inverted shield was probably intended to draw attention to the kins magnanimous forgeiveness of the man who had caused his death a true story first told by roger of howden but with a different thrust it was originally meant to illustrate richards stern unforgiving character since he only pardoned peter basil when he was sure he was going to die but the chronica majora adopted a later popular conception of the generous hearted preux chevalier transforming history into romance suzanne lewis the art of matthew paris in the chronica majora california studies in the history of art vol  university of california press  p   a b andrew holt jonathan phillips crusadesencyclopediacom archived from the original on  december  retrieved  march    stubbs william the constitu